<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Verify correct position of block-level non-replaced elements in normal flow with margin-left applied</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify multiple left margins on block elements in nested scenario are applied." />
        <style type="text/css">
            body
            {
                margin: 0;
            }
            .c1
            {
                margin-left: 10px;
            }
            #d1
            {
                border: solid 1px black;
                background-color: green;
            }
            #d2
            {
                width: 20px;
                height: 20px;
                background-color: blue;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the left edge of the green box is aligned with the right edge of the blue box and the bottom edge of the green box is aligned with the top edge of the blue box.</p>
        <div class="c1">
            <div class="c1" id="d1">ContentFiller</div>
        </div>
        <div id="d2"></div>
    </body>
</html>